latestPosts.caption:
In a heartbreaking turn of events, Liverpool and Portugal footballer Diogo Jota has died in a fatal car accident in Spain. The tragic incident occurred on Thursday in the province of Zamora, near the Sanabria region. According to a report Jota was travelling with his brother, André Jota—also a professional footballer playing for Penafiel in Portugal—when their vehicle veered off the road.
.
Eyewitnesses reported that the car caught fire shortly after the crash, with flames rapidly spreading to nearby vegetation. Emergency services rushed to the scene but were unable to save the 27-year-old footballer.
.
The tragedy comes just 10 days after Jota married his longtime partner, Rute Cardoso. The football world and fans around the globe are mourning the sudden and devastating loss of one of the sport’s brightest talents 
.

latestPosts.caption:
Actress Resham Tipnis addressed the false rumors circulating online that her son Manav had died by suicide in the Kandivali incident. She expressed her anger and concern over the misinformation, confirming that her son is safe and sound. Tipnis vowed to take legal action against those responsible for spreading the fake news. The rumors emerged after a tragic incident in Mumbai involving a 14-year-old boy who died by suicide following an argument with his mother over attending tuition classes. The boy, who lived on the 51st floor of a high-rise building, jumped from an upper floor after a disagreement, leaving everyone in shock. Tipnis's statement put an end to the confusion, reassuring fans and followers that her son is alive and well.
